Pekko SLF4J logging explicitly, e.g. create an ActorSystem with config setting pekko.loggers=[\\\\\\\"org.apache.pekko.event.slf4j.Slf4jLogger\\\\\\\"], pekko.logging-filter=\\\\\\\"org.apache.pekko.event.slf4j.Slf4jLoggingFilter\\\\\\\", and an INFO/DEBUG loglevel. Shut down ActorSystems cleanly. Prefer asserting API behavior or backend receipt rather than exact asynchronous log ordering.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"Without a logging backend, SLF4J 2.x may default to a no-op provider, allowing tests to pass while not exercising the intended logging path.\\\",\\n    \\\"Pekko event-bus logging is asynchronous, so tests that assert emitted log messages may need synchronization or tolerant assertions.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0caacc8d0c484da1016a2b6966442c8195b2faafb34d38ed0b\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"model\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":5063,\"output\":790,\"cacheRead\":12288,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":18141,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1781229916080,\"responseId\":\"resp_0caacc8d0c484da1016a2b695caf8081959f044b90461e9cb3\"}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
